<task id="012" project="ai-procedure-quality-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Create .claude/CHANGELOG.md (forward-only)</title>
    <phase>1</phase>
    <stream>infrastructure</stream>
    <tags>changelog, infrastructure</tags>
    <estimate>20min</estimate>
    <rigor>STANDARD</rigor>
    <parallel-group>1-A</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
    <writes-to>.claude/CHANGELOG.md</writes-to>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    <goal>Establish a curated changelog for procedure-surface changes. Forward-only — no back-fill from history.</goal>
    <context>Per resolved decision #5: forward-only. Git history of .claude/ exists but is hard to query for "when did skill X change?" or "when did the hooks last work?" A curated CHANGELOG.md is the answer.</context>
    <constraints>
      - parallel-safe: false — main session only
      - Forward-only, no back-fill
      - First entry: this project's deliverables
      - Format: Keep a Changelog conventions (https://keepachangelog.com/)
    </constraints>
  </prompt>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/ai-procedure-quality-r1/spec.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step>Create .claude/CHANGELOG.md with header: "Procedure-Surface Changelog — Forward-only from 2026-05-14"</step>
    <step>Add a one-paragraph "How to maintain this" note: every PR that touches .claude/skills/, .claude/agents/, .claude/settings.json, .claude/patterns/, or .claude/constraints/ MUST add an entry to the "Unreleased" section</step>
    <step>Add categories under "Unreleased": Added, Changed, Deprecated, Removed, Fixed</step>
    <step>First release entry: "## [ai-procedure-quality-r1] - 2026-05-14" with the deliverables listed under appropriate categories (researcher subagent under Added, skill template under Added, etc.)</step>
    <step>Reference this CHANGELOG from the new (post-rewrite) CLAUDE.md once Phase 3b lands</step>
  </steps>

  <outputs>
    <output>.claude/CHANGELOG.md</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>File exists with header explaining forward-only convention</criterion>
    <criterion>First release entry contains this project's planned deliverables</criterion>
    <criterion>"How to maintain" instructions are clear enough that the next contributor adds entries without prompting</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
